Russian Farmers Plant 14% More Spring Grains Than Last Year

-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a   a n d   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-05-18T16:06:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/russian-farmers-plant-14-more-spring-grains-than-last-year-1-.html
Russian farmers planted 16.4 million
hectares (40.5 million acres) with spring grains as of today, or
14 percent more than a year earlier, the countryâ€™s  Agriculture
Ministry  said in an e-mailed statement.  About 14.4 million hectares had been sown with grains at
the same point last year, according to the statement. The latest
figure represents 54 percent of the total area earmarked for
sowing. The total spring sowing area, including sugar beet and
oilseeds, reached 27.4 million hectares, or 12 percent more than
a year earlier, the ministry said.  Farmers in the Central federal district planted 3.4 million
hectares with spring grains, or 84 percent of the targeted area.
Plantings in the Southern federal district were 1.8 million
hectares, or 72 percent of the target.  Across  Russia , farmers planted more than 1.2 million
hectares with sugar beets, or 99 percent of the target, and
123,900 hectares more than last year. Sunflower plantings were
67 percent complete at 4.6 million hectares, or 309,100 hectares
more than last year.  To contact the reporters on this story:
